1
00:00:03,379 --> 00:00:05,381
[indistinct chatter]

2
00:00:35,703 --> 00:00:37,997
[BMO] Did you know
there are more stars in the sky

3
00:00:38,080 --> 00:00:41,125
than there are grains of sand in the sky?

4
00:00:41,626 --> 00:00:42,627
It's true.

5
00:00:43,211 --> 00:00:47,256
This is a rare giant asteroid
made entirely of heavy metal.

6
00:00:47,340 --> 00:00:49,926
His name is Lars Darksaber.

7
00:00:50,009 --> 00:00:51,886
I don't know any of these guys.

8
00:00:52,720 --> 00:00:54,764
Whoa. Look at that big boy go!

9
00:00:54,847 --> 00:00:58,059
That's gotta be the biggest comet | ever did-- |...

10
00:00:59,018 --> 00:01:00,186
What the heck?

11
00:01:02,396 --> 00:01:03,940
Let's forget we saw this.

12
00:01:04,523 --> 00:01:09,070
Just another ineffable mystery
in a universe full of mysteries.

13
00:01:13,115 --> 00:01:14,992
| wrote this song for my hat!

14
00:01:15,493 --> 00:01:19,538
J Some people say that space is lonely &

15
00:01:20,206 --> 00:01:24,126
J Silent, empty, sparkling, and immense J

16
00:01:24,794 --> 00:01:30,049
J But wide-open spaces
Put smiles on cowboy faces &

17
00:01:30,132 --> 00:01:34,136
J Even when they're stuck inside their tents &

18
00:01:34,720 --> 00:01:39,058
J If I've got my mission to distract me &

19
00:01:39,642 --> 00:01:44,563
J From friendly folks | had to leave back home J

20
00:01:44,647 --> 00:01:46,649
J And | got my potatoes I

21
00:01:46,732 --> 00:01:49,568
J More exciting than tornadoes J

22
00:01:49,652 --> 00:01:50,653
J Potatoes J

23
00:01:50,736 --> 00:01:52,071
J Potatoes J

24
00:01:52,154 --> 00:01:54,365
J Buy my fresh potatoes &

25
00:01:54,448 --> 00:01:56,909
J Terraforming Martian soil &

26
00:01:56,993 --> 00:01:59,870
J Just put them in a pot to boil &

27
00:02:06,669 --> 00:02:07,920
[yelling]

28
00:02:08,004 --> 00:02:10,006
[suspenseful music playing]

29
00:02:11,841 --> 00:02:13,467
Anybody get mashed?

30
00:02:18,014 --> 00:02:19,390
Alert! Alert!

31
00:02:22,393 --> 00:02:24,270
Time to make the doughnuts.

32
00:02:25,896 --> 00:02:28,232
Boy, that meteoroid storm was scary.

33
00:02:28,316 --> 00:02:31,360
There probably won't be scary cool things on Mars.

34
00:02:33,487 --> 00:02:36,032
It will just be me, alone.

35
00:02:36,615 --> 00:02:38,409
You'll always have me, BMO.

36
00:02:39,035 --> 00:02:42,705
Yes, Football. But | meant new, interesting people.

37
00:02:45,541 --> 00:02:49,670
[BMO] ; I've left my dream of grand adventure &

38
00:02:49,754 --> 00:02:54,467
J For the quiet of my Martian tater farm &

39
00:02:56,802 --> 00:02:57,636
Hi.

40
00:03:00,473 --> 00:03:02,058
You can stretch!

41
00:03:02,141 --> 00:03:03,517
Do you talk?

42
00:03:04,393 --> 00:03:09,732
Oh. Well, you're round and green,
so I'm going to call you Olive.

43
00:03:09,815 --> 00:03:12,151
After my favorite type of bread.

44
00:03:12,234 --> 00:03:13,694
My name is BMO.

45
00:03:18,115 --> 00:03:19,992
[giggles]

46
00:03:22,078 --> 00:03:25,247
You like what you see, huh? You got good taste.

47
00:03:27,291 --> 00:03:28,793
Huh? What are you doing?

48
00:03:32,922 --> 00:03:36,092
[gasps] That was Mars!
We are going the wrong way!

49
00:03:36,175 --> 00:03:37,134
Olive!

50
00:03:40,429 --> 00:03:42,098
[yelling]

51
00:03:42,848 --> 00:03:45,726
So trippy!

52
00:03:48,646 --> 00:03:51,357
No, no, no! The stars are all jacked!

53
00:03:51,440 --> 00:03:54,026
Olive! You interfered with my mission!

54
00:03:54,110 --> 00:03:55,528
[growls]

55
00:03:59,240 --> 00:04:01,033
Okay, | changed my mind!

56
00:04:01,117 --> 00:04:03,160
You can interfere, Olive!

57
00:04:03,244 --> 00:04:04,453
Please!

58
00:04:11,210 --> 00:04:15,464
Fifteen minutes have elapsed.
Subject continues to struggle like a dumdum.

59
00:04:16,048 --> 00:04:17,633
Its attempts are pitiful,

60
00:04:17,716 --> 00:04:19,844
but | am sworn not to interfere.

61
00:04:19,927 --> 00:04:21,470
[watch chiming]

62
00:04:23,431 --> 00:04:24,849
[KS-2] Y4, report!

63
00:04:24,932 --> 00:04:28,310
-1 found a weird bug bot on a rock!
-Hugo's not gonna care about that.

64
00:04:28,394 --> 00:04:32,398
-Don't come back until you find something useful.
-Yes, ma'am.

65
00:04:34,525 --> 00:04:35,526
[sighs]

66
00:04:42,324 --> 00:04:44,326
[suspenseful music playing]

67
00:04:46,996 --> 00:04:48,581
[Y4] This is great!

68
00:04:49,081 --> 00:04:50,207
New entry.

69
00:04:50,291 --> 00:04:54,086
Gray Elves and Shell people are squaring off
over a newly excavated site.

70
00:04:54,170 --> 00:04:55,838
But which side will prevail?

71
00:04:55,921 --> 00:05:00,426
Do the less dominant Shells fail to grasp
the importance of the Elves' unity mission?

72
00:05:00,509 --> 00:05:01,844
Elves!

73
00:05:01,927 --> 00:05:07,600
By the laws of the drift, we assert our claim
to this very sweet photon transmogger.

74
00:05:07,683 --> 00:05:11,020
Heck, no, Cole. The transmogger belongs to Mr. M!

75
00:05:11,103 --> 00:05:14,523
| have the receipt from you. You sold it, man.

76
00:05:14,607 --> 00:05:17,693
That never happened!
And or | don't remember doing it.

77
00:05:17,776 --> 00:05:21,197
We need that part! | challenge you to a drift duel.

78
00:05:21,280 --> 00:05:22,531
One-on-one, Cole.

79
00:05:22,615 --> 00:05:26,869
Last man standing gets the transmogger, aka me.

80
00:05:26,952 --> 00:05:29,705
Oh, you think you're so tough
with your lava blaster.

81
00:05:29,788 --> 00:05:32,625
But it's no match for my... [grunting]

82
00:05:34,001 --> 00:05:35,461
stink sacs!

83
00:05:36,170 --> 00:05:38,547
Such a rare and majestic sight.

84
00:05:38,631 --> 00:05:40,216
[groans] No, thank you.

85
00:05:40,299 --> 00:05:42,801
Ooh. Stink you right up.

86
00:05:42,885 --> 00:05:44,720
On the count of five!

87
00:05:44,803 --> 00:05:45,638
One...

88
00:05:46,222 --> 00:05:47,556
two...

89
00:05:48,224 --> 00:05:49,850
Now, Lenny Longlegs!

90
00:05:51,268 --> 00:05:52,520
Hey! You're cheating!

91
00:05:54,480 --> 00:05:55,648
This is it!

92
00:05:56,398 --> 00:05:58,734
Ha-ha! The elves stand victorious--

93
00:06:04,907 --> 00:06:05,824
It's ruined!

94
00:06:05,908 --> 00:06:07,159
-No!
-No!

95
00:06:07,243 --> 00:06:09,245
[all clamoring]

96
00:06:13,249 --> 00:06:14,500
[laughing]

97
00:06:20,089 --> 00:06:25,469
Whew. | thought that | was toast bread for sure.
But I'm completely uninjured.

98
00:06:28,180 --> 00:06:30,683
Lucky, | didn't crash into anything important.

99
00:06:32,059 --> 00:06:33,519
[all yell]

100
00:06:33,602 --> 00:06:37,398
Huh. You weird babies. That's nothing to cry about.

101
00:06:37,481 --> 00:06:39,358
It's just garbage trash.

102
00:06:39,942 --> 00:06:40,985
Shelves!

103
00:06:41,068 --> 00:06:43,821
Uh-- | mean, elves and Shells.

104
00:06:43,904 --> 00:06:45,364
| propose a truce.

105
00:06:45,447 --> 00:06:47,199
Let us put aside our conflict.

106
00:06:47,283 --> 00:06:48,701
Good babies.

107
00:06:48,784 --> 00:06:50,536
Let us join our forces.

108
00:06:50,619 --> 00:06:53,789
And together, united, destroy that little robot!

109
00:06:54,290 --> 00:06:55,124
What?

110
00:06:55,207 --> 00:06:57,126
[all clamoring]

111
00:06:57,209 --> 00:07:00,045
-Oh, no.
-Get him! After the robot!

112
00:07:00,129 --> 00:07:01,964
But I'm so cute.

113
00:07:02,965 --> 00:07:04,883
-[all] Huh?
-Get them!

114
00:07:04,967 --> 00:07:07,052
[BMO chuckles] You're a rabbit!

115
00:07:07,136 --> 00:07:08,762
[all yelling]

116
00:07:08,846 --> 00:07:09,930
[Shafter] Get him!

117
00:07:11,473 --> 00:07:13,225
[suspenseful music playing]

118
00:07:18,188 --> 00:07:19,106
[yells]

119
00:07:19,189 --> 00:07:20,816
They have terrible aim.

120
00:07:20,899 --> 00:07:22,776
Keep both eyes open!

121
00:07:22,860 --> 00:07:24,320
Robot, what the heck?

122
00:07:24,403 --> 00:07:26,196
Cheese, I'm in trouble!

123
00:07:28,032 --> 00:07:29,241
We'll go around!

124
00:07:32,661 --> 00:07:34,622
[yells, then grunts]

125
00:07:35,831 --> 00:07:36,832
[yells]

126
00:07:37,708 --> 00:07:39,543
[groans] Why did | interfere?

127
00:07:39,627 --> 00:07:42,004
Oh, stupid, stupid, stupid!

128
00:07:42,713 --> 00:07:44,548
[all clamoring]

129
00:07:44,632 --> 00:07:46,050
Tantrum babies.

130
00:07:49,887 --> 00:07:51,805
[indistinct chatter]

131
00:07:51,889 --> 00:07:54,308
[yells] Sorry! Sorry!

132
00:07:55,100 --> 00:07:57,728
Sorry! Sorry! Sorry! Don't hate me!

133
00:07:59,897 --> 00:08:00,898
[yells]

134
00:08:07,571 --> 00:08:10,491
Move over. [grunting]

135
00:08:11,450 --> 00:08:12,326
I'm stuck.

136
00:08:12,409 --> 00:08:13,869
[horn honks]

137
00:08:16,372 --> 00:08:17,414
[Shafter] Mr. M?

138
00:08:19,291 --> 00:08:21,669
Well? Where's the transmogger?

139
00:08:21,752 --> 00:08:24,755
Some little bot came out of nowhere and trashed it!

140
00:08:24,838 --> 00:08:27,091
-But we'll track him down, sir.
-Forget him.

141
00:08:27,174 --> 00:08:29,885
Go back and see if you can salvage the pieces.

142
00:08:29,968 --> 00:08:32,304
Shouldn't we report this to Hugo?

143
00:08:32,388 --> 00:08:34,598
Oh, no need to worry.

144
00:08:34,682 --> 00:08:36,725
I'll take care of that personally.

145
00:08:39,728 --> 00:08:41,563
[Y4] Field log, supplementary.

146
00:08:42,314 --> 00:08:45,275
After, uh, thoughtful consideration,

147
00:08:45,359 --> 00:08:49,905
I've scientifically decided
to take the alien robot in for further study.

148
00:08:49,988 --> 00:08:50,989
Scientifically.

149
00:08:51,573 --> 00:08:54,159
[gasps] So beautiful.

150
00:08:58,414 --> 00:08:59,748
More Olives?

151
00:09:00,666 --> 00:09:02,751
-Finally!
-Huh? Where are we?

152
00:09:03,335 --> 00:09:04,378
[Y4] My secret lab.

153
00:09:05,212 --> 00:09:06,505
[BMO] A secret lab?

154
00:09:08,799 --> 00:09:10,759
[gasps] A secret lab!

155
00:09:10,843 --> 00:09:15,180
It's just how I've always pictured it
for the last two minutes.

156
00:09:15,681 --> 00:09:19,393
-There's gotta be an off switch somewhere.
-[yells] Don't look at my bottom!

157
00:09:19,476 --> 00:09:23,397
It can simulate embarrassment.
Its maker must have been a weirdo.

158
00:09:23,480 --> 00:09:26,567
I'm a self-made man. But who are you?

159
00:09:27,276 --> 00:09:29,486
You can call me Y4. If you must.

160
00:09:29,570 --> 00:09:33,323
No, that's boring. | will call you "Harmonica!"

161
00:09:33,991 --> 00:09:36,660
| don't like that. It's funny though.

162
00:09:36,744 --> 00:09:39,163
| have thought about calling myself something else.

163
00:09:39,246 --> 00:09:40,706
Yeah, that's what | did.

164
00:09:40,789 --> 00:09:44,334
| called myself BMO and the rest is history.

165
00:09:44,418 --> 00:09:47,171
Really? 'Cause it looks
like it's just printed on your side.

166
00:09:47,254 --> 00:09:50,132
Okay. Thank you. Pick a name now.

167
00:09:50,716 --> 00:09:54,011
Okay. Hypothetically, how about...

168
00:09:54,762 --> 00:09:57,848
Y57

169
00:09:58,515 --> 00:09:59,725
| love it!

170
00:10:01,268 --> 00:10:03,020
Y5 will take care of that.

171
00:10:03,854 --> 00:10:07,065
| feel great about this new name.
Begin science log.

172
00:10:07,149 --> 00:10:12,696
The alien robot entity's arm node seems
to be attached by a galaxy standard bolt.

173
00:10:12,780 --> 00:10:15,949
There we go. Good as new.

174
00:10:16,033 --> 00:10:17,117
Hello, BMO.

175
00:10:18,285 --> 00:10:20,871
| guess | gotta knock you out now. For science!

176
00:10:22,790 --> 00:10:23,957
[gasps] Oh.

177
00:10:24,541 --> 00:10:25,501
He's yours?

178
00:10:26,335 --> 00:10:28,754
BMO is his own big boy, thank you.

179
00:10:28,837 --> 00:10:31,507
That old maintenance droid
seems to think you're important.

180
00:10:31,590 --> 00:10:34,551
Olive? She's a no-good-for-nothing troublemaker.

181
00:10:35,719 --> 00:10:37,429
Don't give me that puppy eye.

182
00:10:38,430 --> 00:10:39,264
Serious?

183
00:10:39,348 --> 00:10:41,767
What's the worst a little robot can do?

184
00:10:45,979 --> 00:10:48,732
You know, you guys don't really have
to hang around.

185
00:10:48,816 --> 00:10:52,653
[scoffs] That dang robot has
to come back to this ship eventually.

186
00:10:53,153 --> 00:10:56,615
-Bob, do you have any threes?
-Uh, go fish.

187
00:10:57,491 --> 00:11:01,453
-[gasps] My winning hand!
-1 got a bad feeling.

188
00:11:03,163 --> 00:11:05,165
-[alarm wailing]
-[imitating alarm]

189
00:11:05,249 --> 00:11:07,668
| hear that everywhere | go!

190
00:11:09,753 --> 00:11:11,964
The atmosphere is getting sucked out
of the breach.

191
00:11:12,047 --> 00:11:14,967
-We need to vacate this pod!
-No, | need my ship!

192
00:11:15,050 --> 00:11:18,345
-Your ship is long gone!
-Lead the way, lady.

193
00:11:18,428 --> 00:11:20,597
-[crowd clamoring]
-[Cole] | do not like this!

194
00:11:20,681 --> 00:11:23,517
Come on, Y5! Toward the screaming!

195
00:11:23,600 --> 00:11:27,563
-But that's not what | do!
-It's what | do. Sometimes.

196
00:11:32,025 --> 00:11:33,318
[gasps] Hooray!

197
00:11:33,402 --> 00:11:35,904
| can't stay mad at you, magic skateboard.

198
00:11:36,446 --> 00:11:38,031
Come on, Y5!

199
00:11:41,702 --> 00:11:42,870
[Y5 grunts]

200
00:11:42,953 --> 00:11:46,957
Against all rational thought,
the intrepid researcher returns to the breach to--

201
00:11:47,040 --> 00:11:47,875
Holy!

202
00:11:47,958 --> 00:11:49,877
-[all clamoring]
-Help!

203
00:11:50,919 --> 00:11:52,462
Look at those legs waggle!

204
00:11:52,546 --> 00:11:53,881
Give me the blowtorch.

205
00:11:53,964 --> 00:11:55,173
No. Mine!

206
00:11:55,674 --> 00:11:57,634
-Oh, no!
-[both yelling]

207
00:12:01,221 --> 00:12:03,098
[suspenseful music playing]

208
00:12:03,181 --> 00:12:04,182
Oh.

209
00:12:05,893 --> 00:12:06,894
Hey, wait...

210
00:12:08,604 --> 00:12:11,273
He died as he lived. Sucking bigtime.

211
00:12:12,983 --> 00:12:16,653
Crab guy!
You need to throw your shields all at once.

212
00:12:16,737 --> 00:12:18,739
Uh, no. Why would 1?

213
00:12:18,822 --> 00:12:21,575
Because BMO has a mission.

214
00:12:22,159 --> 00:12:22,993
Shells!

215
00:12:23,076 --> 00:12:25,287
Throw your shields
when the green box commands!

216
00:12:25,370 --> 00:12:26,455
Now!

217
00:12:38,050 --> 00:12:41,929
-Easy like potato pie.
-BMO, that was incredible.

218
00:12:42,012 --> 00:12:44,181
You single-handedly saved everyone!

219
00:12:52,940 --> 00:12:53,774
Olive!

220
00:12:55,192 --> 00:12:57,361
Okay. | know what you're all thinking.

221
00:12:57,444 --> 00:13:00,072
With my ship gone, | am trapped here.

222
00:13:00,155 --> 00:13:03,367
So, yes, | will save your terrible land.

223
00:13:03,951 --> 00:13:06,078
It does need saving, correct?

224
00:13:06,161 --> 00:13:08,163
[power surging]

225
00:13:09,039 --> 00:13:10,165
Yes.

226
00:13:10,248 --> 00:13:13,919
Very well. Then | appoint myself your new sheriff.

227
00:13:17,422 --> 00:13:20,175
Now show me where the trouble is!

228
00:13:20,258 --> 00:13:23,512
Well, there's a lot of trouble in the drift.

229
00:13:32,729 --> 00:13:36,441
Oof. Looks like I'm gonna need a deputy.

230
00:13:40,696 --> 00:13:42,698
-l can't pay you.
-[watch chimes]

231
00:13:48,453 --> 00:13:54,501
BMO, you've just been summoned
to meet some very influential citizens!

232
00:13:54,584 --> 00:13:58,672
That's great! It will give me a chance
to check out my new stomping ground.

233
00:13:59,256 --> 00:14:00,507
Great.

234
00:14:03,802 --> 00:14:06,388
[BMO] Back home,
I'd only walk this far by accident.

235
00:14:06,471 --> 00:14:08,473
[Y5] What was the name
of your home world again?

236
00:14:08,557 --> 00:14:10,225
It is far from here.

237
00:14:10,308 --> 00:14:14,271
A little blue and green planet called BMO World.

238
00:14:15,063 --> 00:14:16,940
Never heard of it.

239
00:14:17,024 --> 00:14:18,817
[sighs, then groans]

240
00:14:19,484 --> 00:14:21,069
| need to make a pit stop.

241
00:14:23,697 --> 00:14:25,073
[BMO] Oh, my goodness!

242
00:14:25,157 --> 00:14:29,327
-[grunts] Hello, big cousin!
-Welcome, Diriftgoer.

243
00:14:29,411 --> 00:14:31,163
It's just a Hugomat.

244
00:14:31,747 --> 00:14:33,165
They're literally everywhere.

245
00:14:37,753 --> 00:14:39,337
[BMO] Cool.

246
00:14:39,421 --> 00:14:42,466
Your sports energy drink is ready.

247
00:14:44,176 --> 00:14:45,260
Whew.

248
00:14:45,343 --> 00:14:49,014
Energy drinks. The future is amazing.

249
00:14:50,223 --> 00:14:52,476
Golly. Did you make all of this?

250
00:14:52,559 --> 00:14:55,687
[Y5] No. | didn't personally
build an ancient space station.

251
00:14:57,147 --> 00:14:58,356
[BMO] Whoa.

252
00:14:58,940 --> 00:15:00,776
Buy my eggs! Buy my eggs!

253
00:15:00,859 --> 00:15:03,236
Or | swear to glob I'll eat them myself!

254
00:15:06,239 --> 00:15:07,532
[creature roars]

255
00:15:08,075 --> 00:15:10,535
[BMO] Hey, check out this hothouse mess.

256
00:15:10,619 --> 00:15:12,996
Nobody goes into jungle pod.

257
00:15:13,080 --> 00:15:17,667
The life-forms have all mutated
into strange and dangerous things.

258
00:15:17,751 --> 00:15:18,627
Come on.

259
00:15:19,878 --> 00:15:21,922
| will play with you, strange things.

260
00:15:26,301 --> 00:15:28,804
Dude, climb with your legs, not your arms.

261
00:15:28,887 --> 00:15:30,514
[sighs] I'm getting tired!

262
00:15:30,597 --> 00:15:34,059
-We're almost there, sweetie! Come on!
-What are you up to?

263
00:15:34,142 --> 00:15:37,145
Uh, well, hello there, Sheriff BMO.

264
00:15:37,229 --> 00:15:41,358
My brother and | are just climbing up
to the coin slot of this Hugomat

265
00:15:41,441 --> 00:15:44,069
for some, uh, exercise.

266
00:15:44,152 --> 00:15:45,112
We love fithess!

267
00:15:45,195 --> 00:15:48,156
You two sound like some fishy four-flushers.

268
00:15:48,240 --> 00:15:50,826
I've got my eye on you. Fishies.

269
00:15:52,410 --> 00:15:53,829
I'm so scared.

270
00:15:58,500 --> 00:16:00,502
[whistle quacking]

271
00:16:02,754 --> 00:16:04,089
What's wrong, partner?

272
00:16:04,172 --> 00:16:08,051
Hey, you're that new guy
who's all over the inter-pod streams.

273
00:16:08,135 --> 00:16:09,427
Yes, | am famous.

274
00:16:09,511 --> 00:16:12,180
Now tell us why you're crying, ugly man.

275
00:16:12,264 --> 00:16:15,308
Well, it's one of my baby space lards.

276
00:16:15,392 --> 00:16:17,769
It won't come back in from stargazing,

277
00:16:17,853 --> 00:16:20,188
which is what | call grazing.

278
00:16:20,272 --> 00:16:22,566
[BMO] They look so cold and scared!

279
00:16:22,649 --> 00:16:25,694
[clicks tongue] BMO lasso!

280
00:16:28,738 --> 00:16:30,991
[BMO grunting]

281
00:16:31,741 --> 00:16:36,371
Man, | don't know what | would have done
if this tender, little baby had frozen

282
00:16:36,955 --> 00:16:39,207
before | could eat it.

283
00:16:39,291 --> 00:16:42,544
-What?!
-You want in on this? | make my own sauce.

284
00:16:42,627 --> 00:16:44,421
-In my sauce gland.
-No!

285
00:16:44,504 --> 00:16:46,006
| saved this lard.

286
00:16:46,089 --> 00:16:49,676
You will repay me by caring for him
and keeping him safe forever.

287
00:16:49,759 --> 00:16:51,178
Also, his name is Ricky!

288
00:16:51,261 --> 00:16:53,430
[whimpers] Yes, sir!

289
00:16:53,513 --> 00:16:54,514
Give me that!

290
00:16:54,598 --> 00:16:59,019
This robot expends energy
in ways that yield it no benefit.

291
00:16:59,102 --> 00:17:00,187
So weird.

292
00:17:01,313 --> 00:17:04,608
[BMO] Deputy! Carry this! | don't have pockets.

293
00:17:06,026 --> 00:17:09,029
-[mellow electronic music playing]
-[Y5] Mmm.

294
00:17:11,448 --> 00:17:13,867
[all yelling]

295
00:17:17,454 --> 00:17:19,331
It's another gravity outage!

296
00:17:22,250 --> 00:17:24,336
[yells, then grunts]

297
00:17:25,253 --> 00:17:27,631
-Blooey.
-This station is trash.

298
00:17:27,714 --> 00:17:29,507
| got my work cut out for me.

299
00:17:29,591 --> 00:17:31,968
Don't worry. Hugo's got a plan to fix things.

300
00:17:32,052 --> 00:17:33,011
Who's Hugo?

301
00:17:33,595 --> 00:17:35,639
[CGO] & Hey, baby, | hear the blues a-calling &

302
00:17:35,722 --> 00:17:38,683
J Tossed salads and scrambled eggs &

303
00:17:38,767 --> 00:17:40,143
Oh, my.

304
00:17:40,852 --> 00:17:44,397
-1 think | know this song.
-Forget about that old robot!

305
00:17:44,481 --> 00:17:46,316
We've got a mission, remember?

306
00:17:46,816 --> 00:17:49,819
[CGO] Good night, Seattle! We love you!

307
00:17:50,403 --> 00:17:52,405
[Y5] 01110000 01110011

308
00:17:52,489 --> 00:17:55,408
01110011 0111001 01110111

309
00:17:55,492 --> 00:17:59,204
01101111 01110010 01100100.

310
00:18:01,289 --> 00:18:03,667
[BMO] Who are we going to see again? | forgot.

311
00:18:04,251 --> 00:18:06,211
[gasps] Bunnies!

312
00:18:06,294 --> 00:18:07,796
So many bunnies.

313
00:18:07,879 --> 00:18:10,632
[chuckles] This one runs a hotel.

314
00:18:11,758 --> 00:18:14,886
[Dad] If he's impressed with it,
our place on the unity pod is a lock.

315
00:18:14,970 --> 00:18:18,056
-[KS-2] If Y4's data isn't flawed, which, you know--
-Um, I'm back. Mom?

316
00:18:18,640 --> 00:18:20,976
Dad? Come look what | found!

317
00:18:21,059 --> 00:18:24,312
Oh, my brain! A functioning service droid!

318
00:18:24,396 --> 00:18:26,523
| haven't seen one of these in forever.

319
00:18:26,606 --> 00:18:28,942
Mom, let me introduce you to...

320
00:18:29,025 --> 00:18:31,444
Howdy, Mom! Nice to meet--

321
00:18:37,867 --> 00:18:41,705
-There's bound to be useful U-pod parts in here.
-We should call Mr. M!

322
00:18:41,788 --> 00:18:43,540
| did good, right?

323
00:18:43,623 --> 00:18:46,751
These are some great parts.

324
00:18:48,128 --> 00:18:49,462
-[rumbling]
-[alarm wailing]

325
00:18:49,546 --> 00:18:50,755
Another failure?

326
00:18:50,839 --> 00:18:52,340
It's in communications pod!

327
00:18:52,424 --> 00:18:54,301
There's never been one this close before.

328
00:18:54,384 --> 00:18:56,803
-What do we do?
-BMO likes alarms.

329
00:18:56,886 --> 00:18:59,306
Y4, hush! The adults are talking.

330
00:19:01,641 --> 00:19:03,810
--meet you! Huh?

331
00:19:04,394 --> 00:19:06,354
BMO! There's a pod in danger!

332
00:19:06,438 --> 00:19:08,315
Let's ride!

333
00:19:08,398 --> 00:19:09,941
[BMO humming]

334
00:19:10,025 --> 00:19:11,067
[KS-2] Y4!

335
00:19:11,151 --> 00:19:12,485
What about Mr. M?

336
00:19:12,569 --> 00:19:15,780
Don't worry. I'll watch over the, uh, parts!

337
00:19:18,575 --> 00:19:20,493
[suspenseful music playing]

338
00:19:29,002 --> 00:19:31,504
Come on, keep printing stuff
we can heist this thing with!

339
00:19:32,088 --> 00:19:34,299
-We gotta bail!
-Wait!

340
00:19:35,425 --> 00:19:37,886
It's our duty to evacuate the citizens!

341
00:19:38,428 --> 00:19:41,306
-I'll save you, weird duck!
-I'm fine!

342
00:19:42,098 --> 00:19:43,016
[gasps]

343
00:19:43,099 --> 00:19:45,685
-Robots can't go in the water!
-Fine!

344
00:19:46,353 --> 00:19:49,939
You are my arms and legs.
Now help me get everyone to safety!

345
00:19:50,023 --> 00:19:51,274
[Bumbo] Excuse me.

346
00:19:51,358 --> 00:19:54,361
We're too small and stupid to save ourselves.

347
00:19:54,444 --> 00:19:55,653
Don't worry, Bumbos.

348
00:19:57,197 --> 00:19:59,574
-[Bumbos] Uh-oh!
-Shush!

349
00:19:59,657 --> 00:20:03,244
Hey! Use your big brain
and think of another way out of here!

350
00:20:03,328 --> 00:20:04,746
Um... Oh!

351
00:20:06,122 --> 00:20:07,665
There's another hatch over this way!

352
00:20:07,749 --> 00:20:10,168
[Bumbos] Hop, hop, hop.

353
00:20:10,251 --> 00:20:11,503
Through here!

354
00:20:11,586 --> 00:20:14,381
Hop. Wait, I think | forgot something.

355
00:20:14,464 --> 00:20:15,965
-Can | go back?
-Get out!

356
00:20:16,049 --> 00:20:18,051
-Okay.
-[Darling & Sweetie] Sheriff!

357
00:20:18,635 --> 00:20:20,970
-We messed up! Sheriff!
-We messed up!

358
00:20:21,054 --> 00:20:22,514
You can swim, right?

359
00:20:22,597 --> 00:20:25,183
-Yes, but badly. Ow!
-Giddyup!

360
00:20:27,852 --> 00:20:28,937
[watch chimes]

361
00:20:29,979 --> 00:20:32,107
-Hello?
-[KS-2] Y4, where are you?

362
00:20:32,649 --> 00:20:35,819
Mr. M is on his way
to pick up that unit for dismemberment.

363
00:20:36,403 --> 00:20:38,154
Heading back now! [yells]

364
00:20:39,406 --> 00:20:41,199
-[9asps]
-What's going on?

365
00:20:41,282 --> 00:20:42,826
[cracking noises]

366
00:20:49,207 --> 00:20:51,501
-[yelling]
-Get me out of here!

367
00:20:52,377 --> 00:20:56,923
Y5, chew through the glass
with your big, nasty teeth. Huh?

368
00:20:57,006 --> 00:20:58,216
Yay, Olive!

369
00:20:59,134 --> 00:21:01,553
-Swing! Swing now!
-[yells]

370
00:21:04,556 --> 00:21:05,807
Jeez, careful much?

371
00:21:05,890 --> 00:21:08,810
-You almost smashed our loot.
-Yeah, watch it next time.

372
00:21:12,188 --> 00:21:14,149
Can't this rabbit swim any faster?

373
00:21:14,232 --> 00:21:15,066
Onit.

374
00:21:16,401 --> 00:21:18,820
-Did you just light a firework on my--?
-[all yelling]

375
00:21:22,991 --> 00:21:24,659
| told you we would make it.

376
00:21:24,742 --> 00:21:26,911
You sure are a worried wart, Olive.

377
00:21:26,995 --> 00:21:30,748
Hey, flatfoot.
We found this thing inside the Hugomat.

378
00:21:30,832 --> 00:21:34,043
We don't know what it does, so it's yours.

379
00:21:35,712 --> 00:21:37,630
Ooh. That's smooth data.

380
00:21:38,840 --> 00:21:40,467
[Y5 groans]

381
00:21:40,550 --> 00:21:42,343
| can't believe | did that.

382
00:21:43,178 --> 00:21:44,471
How did it feel?

383
00:21:45,263 --> 00:21:49,142
-Kind of good, actually.
-Of course.

384
00:21:49,225 --> 00:21:51,227
You're my deputy, after all!

385
00:21:51,811 --> 00:21:52,812
Oh.

386
00:21:53,396 --> 00:21:56,399
Right. Listen, BMO...

387
00:21:56,483 --> 00:21:58,234
Yes, my true friend?

388
00:21:59,986 --> 00:22:03,573
Uh, BMO, there's something | need to tell you.

389
00:22:08,745 --> 00:22:10,413
Get in the car.

390
00:22:11,372 --> 00:22:13,791
We should accept this ride from a stranger.

391
00:22:20,882 --> 00:22:21,758
[sniffs]

392
00:22:23,968 --> 00:22:27,096
This is a pretty sick ride, | gotta say.

393
00:22:27,972 --> 00:22:28,806
[yelps]

394
00:22:32,936 --> 00:22:34,395
[gasps] Is that...?

395
00:22:34,479 --> 00:22:37,774
That's the answer to all the drift's problems.

396
00:22:37,857 --> 00:22:40,610
Behold, the unity pod!

397
00:22:40,693 --> 00:22:42,946
[BMO] Oh, | thought it was a popcorn maker.

398
00:22:43,488 --> 00:22:46,282
Hugo's whipping up
some pretty sweet gadgets in there.

399
00:22:46,366 --> 00:22:49,577
The raddest stuff your little bot eyes will ever see.

400
00:22:49,661 --> 00:22:50,662
Oh, boy!

401
00:22:52,121 --> 00:22:54,541
So, what if Hugo takes BMO apart? It--

402
00:22:54,624 --> 00:22:58,127
It's for the greater good, right?
And I'm all about the greater good.

403
00:22:59,420 --> 00:23:00,421
Greater good!

404
00:23:04,008 --> 00:23:06,219
So many Hugomats.

405
00:23:06,302 --> 00:23:09,180
Yep, yep. | actually came up with those myself.

406
00:23:09,264 --> 00:23:10,682
Isn't that right, boss?

407
00:23:11,766 --> 00:23:16,271
Huh? Uh, yes, the Hugomats were Mr. M's idea.

408
00:23:16,354 --> 00:23:19,524
-Hugo.
-That boy loves flashy gadgets.

409
00:23:19,607 --> 00:23:21,693
Me? I'm more of a pragmatist.

410
00:23:21,776 --> 00:23:24,112
You must be KS-2's daughter.

411
00:23:24,195 --> 00:23:27,574
-Nice to meet you!
-You too, also!

412
00:23:27,657 --> 00:23:30,118
Is this the spicy tech | heard about?

413
00:23:30,201 --> 00:23:32,620
You are so gray and bald!

414
00:23:32,704 --> 00:23:34,539
Ha. Yeah, | am.

415
00:23:35,456 --> 00:23:37,333
Oh, uh... [clears throat]

416
00:23:38,084 --> 00:23:39,294
Noice.

417
00:23:39,377 --> 00:23:40,795
Uh...

418
00:23:42,297 --> 00:23:44,799
Mr. M, why don't you entertain our guests for a bit?

419
00:23:45,550 --> 00:23:48,595
[clicks tongue] You're a kid.
Kids love dumb games, right?

420
00:23:48,678 --> 00:23:50,221
-Um...
-Great!

421
00:23:50,805 --> 00:23:53,308
[humming]

422
00:23:53,391 --> 00:23:55,977
[groans] The greater good.

423
00:23:56,060 --> 00:23:57,812
[ominous music playing]

424
00:24:02,066 --> 00:24:05,153
What do you say we spice things up a bit?

425
00:24:05,236 --> 00:24:08,072
If I win, | get those fancy grav boots.

426
00:24:08,156 --> 00:24:09,741
What? No way!

427
00:24:09,824 --> 00:24:10,867
Oh, come on!

428
00:24:10,950 --> 00:24:13,286
If | lose, you get my fancy boots!

429
00:24:13,828 --> 00:24:16,164
-[groans, then gasps]
-[drill whirring]

430
00:24:16,789 --> 00:24:19,667
[Hugo] Dang. This robot is one of a kind.

431
00:24:20,418 --> 00:24:22,378
But nothing here | can use.

432
00:24:22,462 --> 00:24:23,963
[sighs]

433
00:24:24,047 --> 00:24:27,300
Bummer. Well, maybe next time, KS-2's daughter.

434
00:24:27,383 --> 00:24:31,429
Not so fast! The sheriff is here to help.
Tell me what you need.

435
00:24:32,680 --> 00:24:33,973
Okay.

436
00:24:34,557 --> 00:24:39,479
We've located the final component
for the unity pod, the genesis crystal.

437
00:24:39,562 --> 00:24:43,566
Unfortunately, it lies
within the impenetrable jungle pod.

438
00:24:43,650 --> 00:24:46,736
All our attempts to grab it have been hot "garbo."

439
00:24:46,819 --> 00:24:49,072
So we're engineering our own.

440
00:24:49,822 --> 00:24:51,199
How's it going, guys?

441
00:24:51,658 --> 00:24:54,744
| think we finally cracked it, sir.
Permission to run a test?

442
00:24:54,827 --> 00:24:56,037
[whistles]

443
00:24:56,120 --> 00:24:59,582
[employee]
Cool, cool. Commencing test 325.

444
00:25:03,044 --> 00:25:03,878
Huh?

445
00:25:10,218 --> 00:25:11,928
That-- That shouldn't count!

446
00:25:12,011 --> 00:25:14,764
-Tough beans, kid. A deal's a deal.
-No!

447
00:25:15,348 --> 00:25:18,059
Sorry, Hugo. Please don't be mad.

448
00:25:18,768 --> 00:25:20,978
You are not a very good scientist!

449
00:25:21,062 --> 00:25:23,606
Oh. Reset for test 326.

450
00:25:23,690 --> 00:25:26,150
No. | will get you the real junk!

451
00:25:26,234 --> 00:25:29,195
-What--? Really?
-I'm your huckleberry.

452
00:25:29,278 --> 00:25:31,698
[Mr. M] | gotta agree with the little bot, boss.

453
00:25:31,781 --> 00:25:33,950
He's quick, plants won't eat him.

454
00:25:34,033 --> 00:25:36,202
That's right. Plants hate me!

455
00:25:36,786 --> 00:25:39,914
I'm smelling what you're baking. Smells good.

456
00:25:39,997 --> 00:25:42,709
You know what? Let's try it. What the heck!

457
00:25:42,792 --> 00:25:45,253
-Um, is that--?
-Saddle up, deputy!

458
00:25:45,336 --> 00:25:47,547
We are going to find some treasure!

459
00:25:49,507 --> 00:25:52,719
-Are you really sure about this?
-1 believe in us.

460
00:25:54,595 --> 00:25:57,014
-I'll meet you out front.
-[clicks tongue]

461
00:26:02,687 --> 00:26:05,356
-[both gasp]
-Mom! What, uh...?

462
00:26:05,440 --> 00:26:07,567
There was some kind of accident
in the crystal lab.

463
00:26:07,650 --> 00:26:11,362
-Apparently, the new prototype exploded again.
-[BMO] Oh, Mom.

464
00:26:11,446 --> 00:26:12,905
Don't worry about that fake.

465
00:26:12,989 --> 00:26:16,868
The BMO is headed to the jungle pod right now
to fetch the real one.

466
00:26:17,535 --> 00:26:19,537
Why isn't BMO in a million pieces?

467
00:26:19,620 --> 00:26:21,706
Uh, Hugo didn't need him?

468
00:26:21,789 --> 00:26:23,207
Fantastic.

469
00:26:23,291 --> 00:26:25,501
So we're back at square one.

470
00:26:25,585 --> 00:26:28,254
Lady, stop talking. Come on, sidekick deputy!

471
00:26:28,337 --> 00:26:31,549
What? You're following that little toy's orders?

472
00:26:31,632 --> 00:26:36,053
-No! I'm just following Hugo's orders.
-Y4! Tell me the truth.

473
00:26:40,183 --> 00:26:41,476
I'm sorry, Mom.

474
00:26:41,559 --> 00:26:43,519
| was just humoring it at first.

475
00:26:43,603 --> 00:26:47,732
So we could get to Hugo no fuss.
But | got carried away.

476
00:26:47,815 --> 00:26:50,568
| know I'm not some deputy, all right?

477
00:26:50,651 --> 00:26:53,362
It was just a dumb game.

478
00:26:56,407 --> 00:26:58,075
You two coming or what?

479
00:26:58,659 --> 00:26:59,702
Yeah. | am!

480
00:26:59,786 --> 00:27:03,080
Because I'm the only one around here
that doesn't bite.

481
00:27:04,582 --> 00:27:06,751
[BMO gasps, then groans]

482
00:27:06,834 --> 00:27:08,336
Stop it, bad Olive!

483
00:27:08,961 --> 00:27:12,548
-Olive! Let him go.
-1 don't need your help.

484
00:27:12,632 --> 00:27:16,344
-BMO, I didn't mean to hurt your feelings!
-1 have no feelings!

485
00:27:17,428 --> 00:27:18,763
Forget about her, champ.

486
00:27:18,846 --> 00:27:22,183
Big cool guys like us don't need nobody else.

487
00:27:22,767 --> 00:27:24,352
You make my feelings happy!

488
00:27:28,689 --> 00:27:30,233
[KS-2] Y4, come on!

489
00:27:30,775 --> 00:27:31,818
Yes, ma'am.

490
00:27:40,576 --> 00:27:42,578
[suspenseful music playing]

491
00:27:45,289 --> 00:27:48,376
Yep. This doesn't feel dangerous at all.

492
00:27:48,459 --> 00:27:50,461
[laughing]

493
00:27:52,505 --> 00:27:53,589
Aren't you coming?

494
00:27:53,673 --> 00:27:55,049
Oh, uh, no.

495
00:27:55,132 --> 00:27:57,426
It's real easy to get lost in J-pod.

496
00:27:57,510 --> 00:27:59,762
So I'll be guiding you with this map.

497
00:27:59,846 --> 00:28:03,891
-Oh, but couldn't we bring the map?
-Think fast!

498
00:28:04,684 --> 00:28:07,270
We'll stay in touch through that walkie-talkie.

499
00:28:07,353 --> 00:28:10,356
You'll only be alone in the, uh, literal sense.

500
00:28:10,940 --> 00:28:12,191
BMO is never alone.

501
00:28:12,817 --> 00:28:14,026
Right, Football?

502
00:28:14,110 --> 00:28:16,863
Please. Don't bring me in there, BMO.

503
00:28:19,115 --> 00:28:21,868
[Mr. M] Keep walking straight for 1400 frames.

504
00:28:21,951 --> 00:28:23,077
Copy that.

505
00:28:32,044 --> 00:28:35,464
One thousand two, one thousand and three,
one thousand four...

506
00:28:36,048 --> 00:28:37,758
| don't like this place, BMO.

507
00:28:37,842 --> 00:28:39,844
You are a delicate soul, Football.

508
00:28:39,927 --> 00:28:43,264
But BMO will not be intimidated by nature! [yells]

509
00:28:44,765 --> 00:28:46,559
So pretty.

510
00:28:47,143 --> 00:28:48,811
[Football] BMO, I'm scared.

511
00:28:48,895 --> 00:28:50,021
Oh, Football.

512
00:28:50,104 --> 00:28:54,191
| know you're a scaredy cat,
but | have to complete my mission.

513
00:28:54,734 --> 00:28:59,071
BMO, | think maybe
you're also scared of this mission.

514
00:28:59,155 --> 00:29:00,823
Mm, no.

515
00:29:00,907 --> 00:29:05,161
BMO, if you bonk this up and die,
| couldn't live with myself!

516
00:29:05,244 --> 00:29:07,830
Oh, Football, | won't bonk up.

517
00:29:08,414 --> 00:29:10,291
[yells] Whack! Whack!

518
00:29:14,295 --> 00:29:17,006
[screams, then grunts]

519
00:29:21,218 --> 00:29:23,054
Lucky, this hole was here.

520
00:29:23,721 --> 00:29:24,722
Oh.

521
00:29:24,805 --> 00:29:26,223
Not lucky, BMO.

522
00:29:26,307 --> 00:29:28,142
You are in the dirt hole now.

523
00:29:28,225 --> 00:29:29,644
Dirt hole!

524
00:29:30,394 --> 00:29:32,980
-[screams]
-Run, BMO!

525
00:29:36,025 --> 00:29:37,568
[yelps, then screams]

526
00:29:40,154 --> 00:29:42,156
[suspenseful music playing]

527
00:29:47,453 --> 00:29:48,537
Ew.

528
00:29:59,090 --> 00:30:02,009
[gasps] You're my gross ticket out of here!

529
00:30:02,093 --> 00:30:04,387
Crusty piece of crab!

530
00:30:04,971 --> 00:30:06,097
Fly, Donkus!

531
00:30:14,063 --> 00:30:17,316
Yay! You're my new best friend, Crusty!

532
00:30:18,985 --> 00:30:20,319
Crusty!

533
00:30:20,403 --> 00:30:22,822
[Mr. M] BMO? BMO!

534
00:30:23,823 --> 00:30:25,825
There was a close call, Mr. M.

535
00:30:25,908 --> 00:30:28,327
Mother drift got a taste of BMO.

536
00:30:28,411 --> 00:30:31,580
-But I licked her right back.
-Whose mother?

537
00:30:35,751 --> 00:30:36,836
[KS-2] Y4!

538
00:30:36,919 --> 00:30:39,171
Could you bring me a J-clamp
from out by the--?

539
00:30:39,672 --> 00:30:41,173
Where are your gravity boots?

540
00:30:41,257 --> 00:30:44,010
-1 was playing cards with--
-You gambled?

541
00:30:44,093 --> 00:30:46,345
What? No! It was Mr.--

542
00:30:46,429 --> 00:30:49,557
Honestly, Y4! We'll talk about this later.

543
00:31:02,570 --> 00:31:03,654
Ha!

544
00:31:07,575 --> 00:31:08,409
Wait.

545
00:31:08,492 --> 00:31:10,995
That's another Hugomat stick.

546
00:31:11,871 --> 00:31:13,497
| wonder what's on these.

547
00:31:14,290 --> 00:31:15,416
Wow, okay.

548
00:31:15,499 --> 00:31:17,376
| didn't know you could do that.

549
00:31:18,002 --> 00:31:19,170
Whoa.

550
00:31:19,253 --> 00:31:22,339
-What the heck--?
-Hey, good job, little guy!

551
00:31:22,423 --> 00:31:24,925
You'll be on top of the crystal in a mmm-bop.

552
00:31:27,595 --> 00:31:28,763
[gasps]

553
00:31:28,846 --> 00:31:31,932
It's mad indignant...

554
00:31:32,016 --> 00:31:34,602
All of the Hugomat's are networked.

555
00:31:34,685 --> 00:31:39,231
Mr. M has them identifying useful components
in each pod without anyone knowing.

556
00:31:39,774 --> 00:31:42,359
That's so unethical.

557
00:31:42,443 --> 00:31:43,444
[sighs]

558
00:31:43,527 --> 00:31:45,362
| hope BMO is okay.

559
00:31:45,446 --> 00:31:47,281
| don't feel good about this, BMO.

560
00:31:47,364 --> 00:31:49,450
I'm going to take this crystal, Football.

561
00:31:49,533 --> 00:31:51,035
I'm going to be a hero!

562
00:31:51,118 --> 00:31:52,620
| don't need a deputy!

563
00:31:52,703 --> 00:31:54,955
| don't need anybody!

564
00:31:56,874 --> 00:31:59,293
[creatures screeching]

565
00:32:04,673 --> 00:32:05,925
Shoot, shoot, shoot!

566
00:32:07,802 --> 00:32:11,472
[Y5] Look, Olive! The genesis crystal is moving!

567
00:32:11,555 --> 00:32:13,974
-BMO did it! Wait.
-[beeping]

568
00:32:14,058 --> 00:32:15,226
Wait, wait, wait!

569
00:32:15,309 --> 00:32:17,812
All of the failed pods are missing components.

570
00:32:17,895 --> 00:32:20,898
By taking them, Mr. M is killing the drift.

571
00:32:20,981 --> 00:32:22,650
We have to warn Hugo!

572
00:32:22,733 --> 00:32:24,735
[screaming]

573
00:32:30,241 --> 00:32:31,158
Blood!

574
00:32:31,659 --> 00:32:33,160
Blood-erflies!

575
00:32:34,578 --> 00:32:36,914
Mr. M! | got the crystal!

576
00:32:36,997 --> 00:32:39,500
Throw it here, so you can run faster!

577
00:32:41,085 --> 00:32:42,294
Yes!

578
00:32:42,378 --> 00:32:44,713
Now catch me! [grunts]

579
00:32:46,966 --> 00:32:47,967
Oh.

580
00:32:50,970 --> 00:32:52,179
[whistles]

581
00:32:52,263 --> 00:32:53,973
Very unfortunate.

582
00:32:55,432 --> 00:32:56,559
Oh, BMO.

583
00:32:56,642 --> 00:33:01,480
You tried, but you were never
the hero of the story | like to call "Life."

584
00:33:01,564 --> 00:33:03,983
You were always just the cute sidekick.

585
00:33:04,066 --> 00:33:05,317
Football!

586
00:33:05,401 --> 00:33:07,194
Oh, no, don't cry, BMO.

587
00:33:07,278 --> 00:33:09,155
You know I'm an empath.

588
00:33:09,238 --> 00:33:10,406
-[rustling]
-Huh?

589
00:33:10,489 --> 00:33:12,741
No, no! Football! Help!

590
00:33:12,825 --> 00:33:14,160
BMO!

591
00:33:28,799 --> 00:33:29,633
Oh.

592
00:33:30,676 --> 00:33:33,179
This is probably bad, huh?

593
00:33:35,848 --> 00:33:39,727
[chuckles] | think I'm dying. But that's okay.

594
00:33:39,810 --> 00:33:41,979
BMO always bounces back.

595
00:33:42,062 --> 00:33:44,190
[Purple BMO] Uh-uh. Not this time.

596
00:33:44,773 --> 00:33:47,610
But I'm supposed to save the drift. That's my job.

597
00:33:47,693 --> 00:33:49,528
Now your job is to be dead.

598
00:33:49,612 --> 00:33:50,738
Oh, no.

599
00:33:50,821 --> 00:33:52,740
BMO, you can get through this.

600
00:33:52,823 --> 00:33:54,366
-Really?
-[Green BMO] Just kidding.

601
00:33:54,450 --> 00:33:56,285
[Yellow BMO] You're not a hero.

602
00:33:56,368 --> 00:33:59,038
[all] You're nothing but a little kid, BMO.

603
00:33:59,955 --> 00:34:01,165
Oh...

604
00:34:02,499 --> 00:34:04,960
No. BMO always bounces back.

605
00:34:08,214 --> 00:34:11,383
Hugo! Hugo, Hugo, Hugo!

606
00:34:12,051 --> 00:34:15,137
| never had to do this much exercise
before | ran into BMO-- [grunts]

607
00:34:15,221 --> 00:34:17,348
I've been waiting for those J-clamps.

608
00:34:17,431 --> 00:34:19,934
Mom, look what | grabbed from Mr. M's office!

609
00:34:20,017 --> 00:34:21,602
He's behind all of it.

610
00:34:21,685 --> 00:34:26,523
The drift collapse, the pod failures...
He's a no-good, rooting-tooting four-flusher!

611
00:34:27,107 --> 00:34:30,819
| don't know if those are swear words,
but that sassy robot has messed you up.

612
00:34:31,362 --> 00:34:33,322
[whistling]

613
00:34:33,405 --> 00:34:34,698
What's up, bunnies?

614
00:34:34,782 --> 00:34:36,784
Hopefully nothing slanderous.

615
00:34:36,867 --> 00:34:38,369
| am so sorry, sir.

616
00:34:38,452 --> 00:34:39,703
[gibbers]

617
00:34:41,372 --> 00:34:42,581
No harm done.

618
00:34:43,707 --> 00:34:47,628
Ha! I've already got all the proof
backed up right here!

619
00:34:48,671 --> 00:34:49,672
Woof.

620
00:34:52,049 --> 00:34:53,050
Mom!

621
00:34:53,133 --> 00:34:54,969
-Where's BMO?!
-Bup, bup, bup.

622
00:34:55,052 --> 00:34:58,138
The good news is that he got the genesis crystal.

623
00:34:58,222 --> 00:35:03,227
The even better news is that little BMO died a hero.

624
00:35:03,310 --> 00:35:06,063
-[both] Hurrah!
-No! | have to save him!

625
00:35:06,146 --> 00:35:08,065
-No, Y4!
-[grunts]

626
00:35:08,148 --> 00:35:10,651
My name is Y5.

627
00:35:11,193 --> 00:35:12,528
BMO is my friend.

628
00:35:12,611 --> 00:35:15,948
And | let him down
because | didn't wanna disappoint you.

629
00:35:16,865 --> 00:35:19,535
-Y4!
-Ha! Kids, right?

630
00:35:19,618 --> 00:35:21,912
Always calling out their deadbeat parents.

631
00:35:21,996 --> 00:35:23,289
-What?
-What?

632
00:35:26,292 --> 00:35:27,835
| can't do this alone.

633
00:35:28,502 --> 00:35:31,338
Olive's gone. It's too far to the jungle pod.

634
00:35:31,422 --> 00:35:33,215
I'm too slow!

635
00:35:35,592 --> 00:35:36,468
Huh?

636
00:35:38,929 --> 00:35:41,473
-[whistle quacks]
-[Ricky whistling]

637
00:35:45,978 --> 00:35:47,688
Ricky! [yelps]

638
00:35:47,771 --> 00:35:50,149
Stop. Stop! He's not here.

639
00:35:50,232 --> 00:35:52,192
Listen, BMO's in trouble.

640
00:35:55,279 --> 00:35:57,364
[grunting]

641
00:35:57,448 --> 00:36:01,660
BMO! I'll get you out!

642
00:36:02,161 --> 00:36:02,995
[shrieks]

643
00:36:04,079 --> 00:36:05,456
[screams]

644
00:36:05,539 --> 00:36:07,499
-Stop!
-Hey, back off!

645
00:36:07,583 --> 00:36:09,835
We had to squeeze all these parts out
of a sealed pod.

646
00:36:09,918 --> 00:36:13,047
That's my friend! [sobbing]

647
00:36:13,130 --> 00:36:14,548
I'll sell you the parts.

648
00:36:15,132 --> 00:36:17,217
Ain't this the bunny that saved us?

649
00:36:17,885 --> 00:36:19,094
Please!

650
00:36:19,178 --> 00:36:22,890
The drift is in danger
and BMOQO's the only one people will listen to!

651
00:36:23,891 --> 00:36:25,726
[groans] My conscience gland.

652
00:36:25,809 --> 00:36:27,978
We may know somebody who can help.

653
00:36:30,856 --> 00:36:31,899
Ha-hal!

654
00:36:31,982 --> 00:36:34,860
-Yo, CGO. You up?
-CGO?

655
00:36:36,987 --> 00:36:38,864
| smell that goody scrap.

656
00:36:38,947 --> 00:36:41,075
-| call dibs!
-Make us an offer.

657
00:36:41,158 --> 00:36:42,701
What?! Cut it out!

658
00:36:42,785 --> 00:36:46,789
| mean, ma'am, These two said
you could patch up the sheriff.

659
00:36:46,872 --> 00:36:47,915
Hmm.

660
00:36:47,998 --> 00:36:49,708
This is a moco-bot.

661
00:36:49,792 --> 00:36:52,586
-You know this model?
-I'm practically a cousin.

662
00:36:52,669 --> 00:36:56,382
-A janky, off-brand cousin.
-Yeah, but can you do it though?

663
00:36:57,007 --> 00:36:58,884
Mmm. Probs.

664
00:36:58,967 --> 00:37:00,010
[whoops]

665
00:37:00,094 --> 00:37:04,390
With BMO's cred, we can convince Hugo
to stop Mr. M's schemes.

666
00:37:04,473 --> 00:37:05,557
[CGO] Hugo?

667
00:37:05,641 --> 00:37:09,061
| don't know what you've heard,
but Hugo is the worst.

668
00:37:09,978 --> 00:37:11,313
What do you know?

669
00:37:11,397 --> 00:37:12,606
Uh, duh.

670
00:37:12,689 --> 00:37:15,109
He created me. We go way back.

671
00:37:15,192 --> 00:37:18,237
To the real busted last days of Earth.

672
00:37:20,656 --> 00:37:25,869
Hugo had a big brain and a rocket,
and led an exodus to the stars on the cheap.

673
00:37:25,953 --> 00:37:27,079
[alarm beeps]

674
00:37:28,038 --> 00:37:29,873
[all yelling]

675
00:37:32,209 --> 00:37:36,797
The grays warned him about the dangers
of bio-hacking their alien style,

676
00:37:36,880 --> 00:37:38,715
but Hugo gets his way.

677
00:37:39,550 --> 00:37:41,093
[both] Ahem!

678
00:37:44,930 --> 00:37:46,473
[all yelling]

679
00:37:47,141 --> 00:37:49,143
Then we were saved by a orb.

680
00:37:53,522 --> 00:37:56,233
The drift was already breaking down
when we got here.

681
00:37:56,817 --> 00:37:58,902
But after Hugo set up shop...

682
00:37:58,986 --> 00:38:01,697
Well, he just makes everything worse.

683
00:38:03,031 --> 00:38:04,741
| got chucked into the trash.

684
00:38:05,325 --> 00:38:07,786
That little service droid went back into space.

685
00:38:08,412 --> 00:38:12,207
Poor thing. | wonder if she ever found
what she was looking for.

686
00:38:15,711 --> 00:38:19,298
Hugo's a great guy,
as long as he thinks you're good for something.

687
00:38:26,221 --> 00:38:28,265
Hey, quit leaking on my scrap!

688
00:38:29,224 --> 00:38:30,392
Fingers crossed.

689
00:38:34,271 --> 00:38:36,231
Maybe he needs to warm up a bit.

690
00:38:43,489 --> 00:38:44,323
[whistles]

691
00:38:46,825 --> 00:38:48,285
[power surging]

692
00:38:54,333 --> 00:38:56,752
-[gurgling noise]
-Oop. Was that me?

693
00:38:59,463 --> 00:39:00,422
Oow!

694
00:39:00,506 --> 00:39:04,259
BMO, you have to wake up. | can't fix this.

695
00:39:04,343 --> 00:39:06,470
I'm just a little kid!

696
00:39:07,763 --> 00:39:10,349
[BMO] | said the same thing when | was dying.

697
00:39:10,432 --> 00:39:12,267
[sobbing]

698
00:39:12,351 --> 00:39:15,020
You saved me. You can save the drift.

699
00:39:15,103 --> 00:39:17,272
But it's just too much.

700
00:39:17,356 --> 00:39:19,775
Even when things look really, really stupid,

701
00:39:19,858 --> 00:39:21,944
we still have to try.

702
00:39:24,947 --> 00:39:26,198
[creatures clamoring]

703
00:39:26,782 --> 00:39:28,283
Our suns all went out!

704
00:39:28,367 --> 00:39:29,618
That's nothing.

705
00:39:29,701 --> 00:39:32,871
All our crops are dying. It's gross.

706
00:39:32,955 --> 00:39:36,208
-[watch chimes]
-Oof! Pod fails. They're spreading everywhere.

707
00:39:36,291 --> 00:39:37,709
Y4 was right!

708
00:39:37,793 --> 00:39:40,170
I've never heard you say those words.

709
00:39:40,254 --> 00:39:41,505
Hugo!

710
00:39:41,588 --> 00:39:44,132
You have to shut down the priming sequence!

711
00:39:44,216 --> 00:39:47,010
We're on the verge of station-wide collapse!

712
00:39:47,094 --> 00:39:53,350
Uh-- This is exactly the kind of problem
the unity pod team will be working to prevent.

713
00:39:53,433 --> 00:39:55,936
-Hugocorp gold members, come on up here!
-[Ricky whistles]

714
00:39:56,019 --> 00:39:57,437
[Y5 & BMO yelling]

715
00:40:00,607 --> 00:40:02,109
Everyone, wait!

716
00:40:02,192 --> 00:40:03,819
Hugo's up to no good!

717
00:40:03,902 --> 00:40:06,321
-There's proof in this Hugomat!
-Oh.

718
00:40:06,405 --> 00:40:08,448
Are you trying to get another drive?

719
00:40:09,032 --> 00:40:10,534
Do you still have the data?

720
00:40:10,617 --> 00:40:13,412
That smooth, smooth data.

721
00:40:13,495 --> 00:40:14,955
Right here!

722
00:40:15,998 --> 00:40:17,207
[crowd gasps]

723
00:40:17,291 --> 00:40:19,293
[Y5] You're donking it all up, Hugo!

724
00:40:19,376 --> 00:40:20,502
Do you deny it?

725
00:40:21,378 --> 00:40:23,088
Nah, it's all true.

726
00:40:23,171 --> 00:40:28,468
The unity pod was always designed
to save only myself and my loyal inner circle.

727
00:40:28,552 --> 00:40:30,387
The rest of the drift is...

728
00:40:30,470 --> 00:40:35,142
Well, it's unfortunate collateral damage,
in the grand scheme of things.

729
00:40:35,225 --> 00:40:37,603
Besides, this all can't be on me.

730
00:40:37,686 --> 00:40:40,981
Y'all thought the unity pod
sounded like a sweet deal,

731
00:40:41,064 --> 00:40:44,151
as long as you thought
you were getting a piece of the pie.

732
00:40:44,234 --> 00:40:47,821
But if anyone was offended by my actions,

733
00:40:47,904 --> 00:40:50,032
| am truly, truly...

734
00:40:51,617 --> 00:40:52,743
[chuckles]

735
00:40:53,827 --> 00:40:55,829
[suspenseful music playing]

736
00:40:56,747 --> 00:40:59,041
Well, time for me to get the heck out of here.

737
00:41:00,834 --> 00:41:01,918
Uh-oh.

738
00:41:02,878 --> 00:41:07,758
-There's no way to stop the activation process.
-The station's power will be sucked dry!

739
00:41:07,841 --> 00:41:10,594
No! We were so close.

740
00:41:11,178 --> 00:41:13,180
Why don't we just pull the plug?

741
00:41:13,263 --> 00:41:16,058
If we remove the plug before it's powered up,

742
00:41:17,142 --> 00:41:18,352
it won't turn on.

743
00:41:18,977 --> 00:41:20,312
The robot is right.

744
00:41:20,437 --> 00:41:25,025
The only way we can stop the U-pod from draining
all the juice from the drift is to eject it.

745
00:41:25,108 --> 00:41:27,194
Yes! Brute force!

746
00:41:27,277 --> 00:41:30,781
Everyone, we're going to need a lot of muscle!

747
00:41:30,864 --> 00:41:32,449
| got muscle.

748
00:41:32,532 --> 00:41:34,451
Lard muscle.

749
00:41:34,534 --> 00:41:37,287
Go on! Put your bumps into it!

750
00:41:38,580 --> 00:41:40,791
Swing those shields, Shells!

751
00:41:43,210 --> 00:41:45,545
Use your handsome bodies!

752
00:41:45,629 --> 00:41:47,506
Go, go, go!

753
00:41:47,589 --> 00:41:49,424
Ice that pod!

754
00:41:49,508 --> 00:41:51,843
[all] Go, go, go!

755
00:41:57,891 --> 00:42:00,435
Well, here comes the rascal.

756
00:42:04,773 --> 00:42:07,401
[sighs] We did it. [grunts]

757
00:42:07,484 --> 00:42:09,277
No. We did it!

758
00:42:09,361 --> 00:42:11,029
[all cheering]

759
00:42:11,988 --> 00:42:13,073
Hold up, everyone!

760
00:42:13,156 --> 00:42:17,953
| don't wanna be a downer, but we just launched
all of our best resources into space.

761
00:42:19,162 --> 00:42:20,956
Is it too late to get on the U-pod?

762
00:42:26,128 --> 00:42:27,254
[Y5] It's true.

763
00:42:27,337 --> 00:42:31,216
Most of the station is dead now
and all communications are down.

764
00:42:31,299 --> 00:42:34,511
We're going to have to manage
the remaining resources to survive.

765
00:42:34,594 --> 00:42:36,638
We need to learn how to help each other.

766
00:42:36,722 --> 00:42:39,558
| know it's hard, but we have to try.

767
00:42:40,183 --> 00:42:41,435
Or we won't make it.

768
00:42:42,352 --> 00:42:44,229
Ahem. I'll give it a shot.

769
00:42:44,312 --> 00:42:45,188
Yeah!

770
00:42:45,272 --> 00:42:50,152
-We can teach y'all how to steal and, uh...
-Forage for spare parts in the defunct pods.

771
00:42:50,235 --> 00:42:52,487
We'll rebuild Hugo's old lab.

772
00:42:52,571 --> 00:42:55,490
Maybe we can find some non-apocalyptic energy.

773
00:42:56,074 --> 00:42:58,201
-[creature] Yeah.
-[KS-2] Y57

774
00:42:59,077 --> 00:43:00,495
Can you forgive us?

775
00:43:00,579 --> 00:43:05,250
We were so focused on getting our family
to a better place that we lost our way.

776
00:43:05,333 --> 00:43:07,753
[KS-2] You're an amazing person, Y5.

777
00:43:12,174 --> 00:43:15,260
Yep, it's time for this sheriff to move on.

778
00:43:16,678 --> 00:43:20,307
Ricky! Let's ride! Yee-haw!

779
00:43:32,861 --> 00:43:34,529
-[rustling]
-Huh?

780
00:43:36,782 --> 00:43:39,868
Oh, it's you. Still disappointed in me?

781
00:43:42,204 --> 00:43:43,538
[scoffs]

782
00:43:43,622 --> 00:43:46,291
And | grabbed as many snacks as | wanted.

783
00:43:46,374 --> 00:43:47,667
The end!

784
00:43:48,418 --> 00:43:51,421
| should tell that story to Y5 next time | see her.

785
00:43:51,505 --> 00:43:54,341
| bet she will be mayor by then. [giggles]

786
00:43:54,966 --> 00:43:55,801
Huh?

787
00:43:56,426 --> 00:43:57,803
We are here!

788
00:43:57,886 --> 00:43:59,221
| will strap in.

789
00:44:10,106 --> 00:44:11,608
Ricky, you beast!

790
00:44:11,691 --> 00:44:13,944
Now go! Be free!

791
00:44:14,027 --> 00:44:15,612
My name is Twinkletoes.

792
00:44:15,695 --> 00:44:17,072
[BMO] Oh. Okay.

793
00:44:25,372 --> 00:44:27,332
[chuckles] Who's that?

794
00:44:33,046 --> 00:44:35,048
[upbeat music playing]

